('602', 'Jacquetta Barber', 'barber.jacquetta@hotmail.com', 'Stop Losing Sales by Fixing This Common Mistake', '2087855429', 'Dan Kennedy has seen it time and againâ€”businesses, from small shops to multi-billion-dollar giants, making the same costly mistake: treating advertising, marketing, and sales as three separate, disconnected silos.\r\n\r\nAdvertising is outsourced to an agency. Marketing is tossed to an in-house team that often lacks real direct response chops. And sales? Itâ€™s left to operate on its own, often finding out about ad campaigns only after seeing them online or in a magazine.\r\n\r\nDan calls it what it is: an inefficient, expensive mess. And itâ€™s more common than youâ€™d think.\r\n\r\nHereâ€™s the real problem with this disconnected approach:\r\n\r\nWhen advertising and marketing flood the funnel with unqualified leads, it doesnâ€™t just waste moneyâ€”it drives away your best closers. Instead of focusing on selling, theyâ€™re buried in garbage leads. Frustrated and underused, your top performers donâ€™t stick around. They take their talent elsewhere, and youâ€™re left with a mediocre team struggling to hit quota.\r\n\r\nDan Kennedy says the solution is simpleâ€”but rarely implemented: Integration.\r\n\r\nYour advertising, marketing, and sales efforts must work in harmony. When they do, your sales team can focus exclusively on what they do bestâ€”closing deals.\r\n\r\nHereâ€™s how Dan recommends structuring the process:\r\n\r\nLead Generation brings in only high-quality, pre-qualified prospects.\r\n\r\nMarketing nurtures those leads, building trust and guiding them toward the buying decision.\r\n\r\nSales swoops in at the right moment to close, onboard, and potentially upsell or retain.\r\n\r\nDan often compares it to a world-class hospital. If youâ€™re the Cleveland Clinic, you donâ€™t have your top heart surgeon giving community lectures, screening patients, or sweeping floors. You want them in the operating room doing what only they can doâ€”saving lives.\r\n\r\nThe same logic applies to your sales team.\r\nYour closers should be doing one thing: closing. Not chasing cold leads. Not doing follow-ups. Not dialing dead-end phone numbers. Thatâ€™s a waste of elite talent.\r\n\r\nTo build a business like this, Dan emphasizes one core principle: start with the end in mind.\r\n\r\nAsk yourself:\r\n\r\nWhat does the ideal, sales-ready lead look like?\r\n\r\nWhat marketing process gets them to that point?\r\n\r\nWhat lead gen strategy attracts those people in the first place?\r\n\r\nOnce you have the answers, you reverse-engineer the system. Thatâ€™s how you create a high-performance machineâ€”where every part fuels the next, and your best people are doing their highest-value work.\r\n\r\nIf this approach resonates with youâ€”and youâ€™re ready to eliminate the disconnect in your businessâ€”Dan Kennedy lays it all out in his book,\r\nâ€śThe NO B.S. Direct Marketing for Non-Direct Marketing Businesses.â€ť\r\n\r\ní ˝í±‰ Click Here to Claim Your FREE Copy and Unlock Over $6,193 in Bonuses\r\nhttps://marketersmentor.com/direct-marketing-book.php?refer=ngnmotors.co.uk&real=yes\r\n\r\nHereâ€™s what youâ€™ll get when you order today:\r\n\r\nThe Direct Marketing Toolkit â€“ a playbook for building a system that unites lead gen, marketing, and sales.\r\n\r\n4-Hour Elite Marketing Intensive â€“ featuring 21 of the worldâ€™s top marketers revealing their #1 ROI-driving strategy.\r\n\r\nClick here to get everything now â†’\r\nhttps://marketersmentor.com/direct-marketing-book.php?refer=ngnmotors.co.uk&real=yes\r\n\r\nDedicated to Multiplying Your Income,\r\nJacquetta\r\n\r\nP.S. Dan always says:\r\nWhoever can spend the most money to acquire a customerâ€”wins.\r\nAn integrated system helps you do that with precision and profitability.\r\n\r\n\r\nUnsubscribe: \r\nhttps://marketersmentor.com/unsubscribe.php?d=ngnmotors.co.uk&real=yes', '2025-04-19 03:43:09', '2025-04-19 03:43:09', NULL),
